WEBVTT

00:03.409 --> 00:06.410
[music playing]

00:32.339 --> 00:33.800
[tires screeching]

00:33.835 --> 00:36.803
[dramatic music]

01:02.171 --> 01:02.763
Please!

01:02.798 --> 01:03.368
Please!

01:08.177 --> 01:08.769
Help me!

01:12.775 --> 01:14.742
Help me!

01:14.777 --> 01:17.712
[crying]

01:45.709 --> 01:47.445
Pushed, you think?

01:47.480 --> 01:50.217
Yeah, or jumped or fell,
but no blood up here, though,

01:50.252 --> 01:53.616
so she was shot down there.

01:53.651 --> 01:55.222
Pushed, jumped, or fell.

01:55.257 --> 01:57.224
Shot in the back of the
head, dragging herself away.

02:00.493 --> 02:01.525
My god, that's awful.

02:05.498 --> 02:08.202
I hope we didn't pull you
away from the lovely Rita.

02:08.237 --> 02:09.632
Is that how this
is going to go?

02:09.667 --> 02:11.634
Rita's sprinkled into
every conversation now?

02:11.669 --> 02:13.735
Oh, of course not.

02:13.770 --> 02:15.803
Except yeah.

02:15.838 --> 02:19.136
But it's good, though.

02:19.171 --> 02:21.138
Last week, we would pulled
you away from, what,

02:21.173 --> 02:22.579
a can of soup and Jeopardy?

02:22.614 --> 02:23.976
You know what?

02:24.011 --> 02:25.219
There's nothing wrong
with soup and Jeopardy.

02:25.254 --> 02:26.715
They happen to
complement one another.

02:26.750 --> 02:28.849
The vehicle's registered
to Maggie Moore.

02:28.884 --> 02:30.521
Lives a few miles from here.

02:30.556 --> 02:31.588
You sent Maggie Moore?

02:31.623 --> 02:32.589
Weird, right?

02:32.624 --> 02:36.087
[music playing]

02:53.612 --> 02:56.041
So, did she take the
ring back, your wife?

02:56.076 --> 02:57.713
Nope.

02:57.748 --> 02:59.583
Unbeknownst to me., I entered
into a marriage contract,

02:59.618 --> 03:02.520
and she's entitled
to certain niceties.

03:02.555 --> 03:03.785
Niceties?

03:03.820 --> 03:06.524
The fuck is that?

03:06.559 --> 03:07.789
What the hell, man?

03:07.824 --> 03:08.856
Oh, it's fine.

03:08.891 --> 03:09.692
You just cut it off.

03:09.727 --> 03:10.693
Yes, not fine.

03:10.728 --> 03:11.892
This is fucking mold.

03:11.927 --> 03:13.366
It's just not edible.

03:13.401 --> 03:15.401
You know, you're paying
me $0.20 on the dollar.

03:15.436 --> 03:16.732
It's eat-able enough.

03:16.767 --> 03:17.601
Edible.

03:17.636 --> 03:21.099
Edible enough, Jesus.

03:21.134 --> 03:23.277
Marriage contract--
that's a thing?

03:23.312 --> 03:24.872
Yeah.

03:24.907 --> 03:27.105
Her shrink says I promised
Maggie I'd make big money.

03:27.140 --> 03:29.613
Fuck me if I'm running
behind schedule.

03:29.648 --> 03:31.142
But she bitches I'm
pinching pennies.

03:31.177 --> 03:33.551
I'm pinching fucking pennies.

03:33.586 --> 03:37.115
Try not buying $600 rings,
and let me get back on track.

03:37.150 --> 03:38.215
Yeah, simple math.

03:38.250 --> 03:40.459
Yes, simple math, right?

03:40.494 --> 03:42.428
But no, here I am,
serving up fucking

03:42.463 --> 03:45.794
expired food to make more money
to pay her shrink to tell her

03:45.829 --> 03:48.401
I'm pinching fucking pennies.

03:48.436 --> 03:50.095
Where's my shit?

03:50.130 --> 03:51.965
We're having a conversation.

03:52.000 --> 03:52.900
Yeah, you told me.

03:52.935 --> 03:54.033
Now, where's my shit?

04:04.309 --> 04:05.682
Don't tell me you lost it.

04:05.717 --> 04:07.079
That's some sensitive shit.

04:07.114 --> 04:07.684
Fuck me.

04:23.570 --> 04:24.162
Hey, Mags?

04:28.036 --> 04:28.639
Maggie?

04:40.752 --> 04:41.355
Mags!

04:46.923 --> 04:47.988
Hey, Mags.

04:48.023 --> 04:49.561
You OK?

04:49.596 --> 04:53.664
What kind of monster are you?

04:53.699 --> 04:57.162
Whatever that
is, it is not mine.

04:57.197 --> 04:57.899
You're lying.

04:57.934 --> 04:58.636
I'm not.
I'm not.

04:58.671 --> 04:59.802
I'm not.

04:59.837 --> 05:00.506
It's this work
guy, Tommy, Jesus.

05:00.541 --> 05:01.507
I swear to God.

05:01.542 --> 05:02.673
Don't you dare swear to God.

05:02.708 --> 05:05.170
You're not entitled
to swear to God.

05:05.205 --> 05:07.381
Jesus, what the
fuck is in there?

05:07.416 --> 05:13.343
Pictures of children,
of little children.

05:13.378 --> 05:15.048
Holy shit.

05:15.083 --> 05:18.018
I had nothing to do with that,
Maggie, and I mean nothing.

05:18.053 --> 05:19.723
I was just passing them along.

05:19.758 --> 05:24.321
MAGGIE: You brought this filth
into our home, into my home.

05:24.356 --> 05:25.894
Why do you have anything
to do with this freak?

05:25.929 --> 05:27.357
JAY: OK, he's a piece
of shit, all right?

05:27.392 --> 05:28.325
You think I don't know that?

05:28.360 --> 05:29.535
But those are not mine.

05:29.570 --> 05:31.702
You're providing them.

05:31.737 --> 05:35.068
This is a crime, and
you are an accessory!

05:35.103 --> 05:37.367
And that's if I
even believe you!

05:37.402 --> 05:39.611
What the fuck does that mean?

05:39.646 --> 05:41.415
You think I get
off on that shit?

05:41.450 --> 05:43.373
I don't know what
you get off on, Jay.

05:43.408 --> 05:44.946
JAY: It's just part of the deal.

05:44.981 --> 05:48.081
I pass along the packages,
and I get cheap food.

05:48.116 --> 05:49.588
If you can't figure
out how to make a buck,

05:49.623 --> 05:52.349
that's fine, but this?

05:52.384 --> 05:53.889
You need to leave!

05:53.924 --> 05:55.055
JAY: Oh, I need to leave?

05:55.090 --> 05:56.353
Yeah!

05:56.388 --> 05:57.563
This is my house,
Maggie, and I'm not

05:57.598 --> 05:59.257
leaving my own fucking house!

05:59.292 --> 06:00.599
I'm calling the cops.

06:00.634 --> 06:02.700
Hey, hey, do not--
do not call the cops!

06:02.735 --> 06:06.198
Get out, I said.

06:06.233 --> 06:08.640
[music playing]

06:10.435 --> 06:11.104
JAY: Fuck you, Mags!

06:25.857 --> 06:28.429
[tires screeching]

06:31.797 --> 06:33.797
Hey, are you crazy with this?

06:33.832 --> 06:34.963
Are you fucking insane?

06:34.998 --> 06:36.602
Maggie found those
pictures, man.

06:36.637 --> 06:37.570
Oh, we had an agreement, man.

06:37.605 --> 06:38.736
My business is my business.

06:38.771 --> 06:39.935
Nobody told you to open it.

06:39.970 --> 06:40.969
Yeah, well, I didn't open it.

06:41.004 --> 06:41.805
Maggie opened it.

06:41.840 --> 06:43.136
She threw me out.

06:43.171 --> 06:44.643
Oh, maybe she's using
that as an excuse.

06:44.678 --> 06:46.073
Maybe she's like
banging someone else.

06:46.108 --> 06:46.744
[grunting]
- What?

06:46.779 --> 06:48.009
No, she's not.

06:48.044 --> 06:49.483
Jesus.

06:49.518 --> 06:50.341
You're the one who should
be seeing a shrink,

06:50.376 --> 06:51.441
you fucking perv.

06:51.476 --> 06:52.409
What the hell is wrong with you?

06:52.444 --> 06:54.411
Hey, man, we had a deal.

06:54.446 --> 06:55.247
I do for you.

06:55.282 --> 06:56.248
Then you do for me.

06:56.283 --> 06:57.447
Now you take another side?

06:57.482 --> 06:59.119
That's fucking
Stockholm syndrome.

06:59.154 --> 07:00.824
OK, that is not Stockholm
syndrome, you fucking maniac.

07:00.859 --> 07:02.023
That's Stockholm syndrome.

07:02.058 --> 07:03.794
No, that is not
Stockholm syndrome.

07:03.829 --> 07:05.763
Stockholm syndrome is when you
get kidnapped and brainwashed.

07:05.798 --> 07:08.458
God damn it, are
you fucking thick?

07:08.493 --> 07:10.768
Oh, she's going to clean me out.

07:10.803 --> 07:11.428
So fucking what?

07:11.463 --> 07:12.363
Stay here, man.

07:12.398 --> 07:13.870
You got a can.

07:13.905 --> 07:16.708
You got a full kitchen,
hella meat, cheese, and--

07:16.743 --> 07:19.271
Oh, yeah, yeah, that's
my dream fucking scenario.

07:19.306 --> 07:21.548
Fuck, what if she goes to
the cops with those pictures?

07:21.583 --> 07:23.946
Then I'm an accessory
to your sick shit-- ah!

07:23.981 --> 07:24.518
Fuck!

07:24.553 --> 07:26.850
Ow!

07:26.885 --> 07:28.885
I got fucking plans, man!

07:28.920 --> 07:31.888
So it's best to keep me
out of the situation!

07:31.923 --> 07:34.055
So if you need help getting
those pictures back,

07:34.090 --> 07:37.322
which you better fucking
do, I know a guy.

07:39.898 --> 07:40.831
Ah!

07:40.866 --> 07:42.294
You understand?

07:42.329 --> 07:43.229
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

07:43.264 --> 07:43.966
I'll handle it.

07:44.001 --> 07:45.803
I'll handle it.

07:45.838 --> 07:48.168
Ah, oh.

07:48.203 --> 07:49.367
I want my fucking pictures!

07:53.241 --> 07:56.143
His life had taken
an unexpected turn.

07:56.178 --> 07:59.212
Every night, he ate a can
of soup in front of the TV,

07:59.247 --> 08:03.315
usually Jeopardy unless
a ballgame was on.

08:03.350 --> 08:06.890
His friends would call, but
he didn't want to see them.

08:06.925 --> 08:09.354
He didn't want their
well meaning pity.

08:09.389 --> 08:12.423
But it wasn't just that.

08:12.458 --> 08:15.932
For years, he had
the perfect life.

08:15.967 --> 08:18.572
It was too hard for him
to admit it was over.

08:26.978 --> 08:29.110
So was that autobiographical?

08:29.145 --> 08:32.047
Oh, no, just madeup stuff.

08:32.082 --> 08:33.884
I thought it
was really moving.

08:33.919 --> 08:36.447
How long you been writing?

08:36.482 --> 08:38.086
I wouldn't really
call it writing,

08:38.121 --> 08:39.692
but I've been playing around
with it since high school.

08:39.727 --> 08:41.694
This high school, in fact.

08:41.729 --> 08:43.289
Huh.

08:43.324 --> 08:44.763
Here.

08:44.798 --> 08:46.523
Defacing public property.

08:46.558 --> 08:47.392
Wow.

08:47.427 --> 08:49.394
So you were a hooligan.

08:49.429 --> 08:51.561
Well, I have since reformed.

08:51.596 --> 08:54.102
Glad to hear it.

08:54.137 --> 08:59.811
Hey, I was going to grab
a coffee down the street

08:59.846 --> 09:01.241
if you want to join me maybe.

09:01.276 --> 09:03.045
Oh, uh--

09:03.080 --> 09:04.816
Come on.

09:04.851 --> 09:07.346
You'll be miserable for 20
minutes tops, I promise.

09:15.587 --> 09:18.555
You know, sometimes,
in conversation,

09:18.590 --> 09:21.096
the other person might
ask, for instance,

09:21.131 --> 09:24.594
how long they've been writing,
you know, just as an example.

09:24.629 --> 09:26.563
Coincidentally,
I was just going

09:26.598 --> 09:30.468
to ask, even before
you mentioned that,

09:30.503 --> 09:32.239
how long have you been writing?

09:32.274 --> 09:35.847
Well, I got my first
diary on my 10th birthday

09:35.882 --> 09:39.950
and then tore through one
a month till I was 23.

09:39.985 --> 09:41.655
What happened to 23?

09:41.690 --> 09:45.417
Mm, got married, had a child
two months later-- my parents

09:45.452 --> 09:47.023
not happy about that.

09:47.058 --> 09:51.060
And 12 years flew
by, and here I am.

09:57.002 --> 10:00.971
Uh, so you're
married with a kid?

10:01.006 --> 10:05.943
Mm, I'm separated
with two kids.

10:05.978 --> 10:08.275
So what about you?

10:08.310 --> 10:12.180
What's your situation?

10:12.215 --> 10:13.346
No kids.

10:13.381 --> 10:14.050
No kids.

10:14.085 --> 10:16.822
My wife passed.

10:16.857 --> 10:20.056
Wow, I'm sorry.

10:20.091 --> 10:22.729
You know, life.

10:22.764 --> 10:24.797
It's what happens
while you're busy making

10:24.832 --> 10:29.901
other plans, which is not a
John Lennon quote, by the way.

10:29.936 --> 10:31.298
No, it is actually from a--

10:31.333 --> 10:33.740
[voice fading out]

10:33.775 --> 10:37.238
[leaf blower]

10:45.754 --> 10:46.511
Hey.

10:46.546 --> 10:47.644
Hey, Mags.

10:47.679 --> 10:49.217
I told you to stay away.

10:49.252 --> 10:50.922
I'm just getting it nice
and neat the way you like it.

10:50.957 --> 10:51.549
Come on.

10:51.584 --> 10:52.253
Come on.

10:52.288 --> 10:53.419
We got to talk.

10:53.454 --> 10:54.519
You're not answering the phone.

10:54.554 --> 10:55.553
Because I don't want to talk.

10:55.588 --> 10:56.829
You see how that works?

10:56.864 --> 10:58.655
And don't you dare
come by the diner.

10:58.690 --> 11:00.767
Hey, Mags, listen to me.

11:00.802 --> 11:02.769
Hey, listen.

11:02.804 --> 11:05.563
I know you're pissed, but
do not go to the cops.

11:05.598 --> 11:08.005
This guy, Tommy T,
he's a complete psycho.

11:08.040 --> 11:11.173
You go to the cops, I don't
know what he's going to do.

11:11.208 --> 11:12.240
To you or to me?

11:12.275 --> 11:14.572
You, me, both of us.

11:14.607 --> 11:16.673
But I'm worried about you.

11:16.708 --> 11:20.248
[scoffs] Fuck you, Jay!

11:20.283 --> 11:21.546
My lawyer's calling you.

11:21.581 --> 11:23.680
Waste your bullshit on her.

11:23.715 --> 11:26.287
You're calling a lawyer?

11:26.322 --> 11:27.761
Mags, come on.

11:27.796 --> 11:29.290
Mags!

11:29.325 --> 11:31.930
Seriously?

11:31.965 --> 11:35.527
What, did your shrink
tell you to do that?

11:35.562 --> 11:37.034
[gong]

11:37.069 --> 11:40.004
[asian music]

11:46.980 --> 11:49.277
You know, if you don't
mind, actually, I'm

11:49.312 --> 11:51.477
a little sore today, the
neck and shoulders area.

11:51.512 --> 11:52.643
Oh.

11:52.678 --> 11:54.282
First time for
everything, right?

11:54.317 --> 11:58.188
[chuckles] Yeah, I
got a lot of stress.

12:01.258 --> 12:04.754
Yeah, got a lot of decisions
to make that's going to affect

12:04.789 --> 12:09.000
my lifestyle, my
disposable income.

12:09.035 --> 12:11.904
You know Castle Subs,
Indian school in Highland?

12:11.939 --> 12:14.005
That was a sub place?

12:14.040 --> 12:18.570
Yeah, it's a sub
place, Castle Subs?

12:18.605 --> 12:21.177
I'm a franchisee.

12:21.212 --> 12:24.246
Just the one place for
now, but down the road,

12:24.281 --> 12:27.777
I imagine six, maybe
seven establishments.

12:27.812 --> 12:30.582
And then from there, you
know, sky's the limit.

12:30.617 --> 12:33.321
You know Howard Schultz?

12:33.356 --> 12:36.962
Starbucks guy, who
owns half the planet?

12:36.997 --> 12:39.360
I'm going to own the other half.

12:39.395 --> 12:40.592
Big dreams.

12:40.627 --> 12:42.297
What's stopping you?

12:42.332 --> 12:47.467
Nothing's stopping me, except
the potential legal impediment

12:47.502 --> 12:50.140
from my wife, of all people.

12:50.175 --> 12:52.670
Can you believe that?

12:52.705 --> 12:54.540
What would Starbucks guy do?

12:54.575 --> 12:57.543
[music playing]

13:05.520 --> 13:08.389
Hey, Tommy T. Set it up.

13:23.736 --> 13:26.704
[tv playing distantly]

13:50.400 --> 13:53.368
[knocking]

13:53.403 --> 13:56.569
Mr. Cosco!

13:56.604 --> 13:59.572
[planes flying on tv]

14:25.798 --> 14:27.303
Pretty loud, don't you think?

14:33.245 --> 14:34.244
[tv stops]

14:39.988 --> 14:42.483
Tommy T fill you in?

14:42.518 --> 14:44.287
My situation, he explain it?

14:48.161 --> 14:50.524
What, you got
laryngitis or something?

14:53.199 --> 14:56.068
Oh, you're deaf?

14:56.103 --> 14:56.893
Seriously?

14:56.928 --> 14:57.597
You're fucking deaf?

15:02.472 --> 15:05.770
So-- so you read lips?

15:08.544 --> 15:12.018
Oh, Jesus, OK.

15:12.053 --> 15:13.349
[shredding]

15:13.384 --> 15:16.484
Yeah, smart.

15:16.519 --> 15:17.518
No paper trail.

15:17.553 --> 15:18.354
I like that.

15:22.393 --> 15:31.367
OK, so, uh, my wife,
she is threatening

15:31.402 --> 15:34.634
to go to the cops over
some shit that Tommy T got

15:34.669 --> 15:36.867
involved with-- no judgment.

15:36.902 --> 15:42.279
So basically what I would
like from you is to scare her

15:42.314 --> 15:48.351
off the idea, which, you know,
ultimately is for the best

15:48.386 --> 15:52.190
because you know Tommy
T is no fucking angel.

15:56.988 --> 16:00.066
So that's why you didn't know
the TV was so fucking loud.

16:03.566 --> 16:05.896
As soon as possible.

16:05.931 --> 16:09.372
Yeah, you're really
doing me a solid, man.

16:09.407 --> 16:10.967
So tell you what?

16:11.002 --> 16:13.244
Free food at my
sub shop for life.

16:15.776 --> 16:16.742
It's a perk.

16:16.777 --> 16:18.216
You know, not like your fee.

16:24.950 --> 16:27.885
[shredding]

16:32.364 --> 16:35.728
And let me get a mega bowl.

16:35.763 --> 16:38.566
Ugh, can you even
imagine this much money?

16:38.601 --> 16:40.073
I wouldn't even
know where to start.

16:40.108 --> 16:41.569
Pretty sure the
taxes on the lump sum

16:41.604 --> 16:44.341
are like half, though, right?

16:44.376 --> 16:45.705
Yeah, I don't know.

16:45.740 --> 16:47.674
Yeah, pretty sure they are.

16:47.709 --> 16:51.249
I mean, I could live OK on
$100 million, though, right?

16:51.284 --> 16:52.041
What was the number?

16:52.076 --> 16:53.944
I just want to pay.

16:53.979 --> 16:55.880
No, you don't want to
miss out on these rewards.

16:55.915 --> 16:57.948
What's your phone?

16:57.983 --> 17:04.460
928-965-2541.

17:04.495 --> 17:06.231
Maggie Moore.

17:06.266 --> 17:07.793
JAY: My wife.

17:07.828 --> 17:09.531
Got it.

17:09.566 --> 17:11.368
Would you like to add your
name to the loyalty membership?

17:11.403 --> 17:12.600
Nope.

17:12.635 --> 17:13.766
OK, then we'll keep
it just your wife

17:13.801 --> 17:15.735
then on Hanover Court.

17:15.770 --> 17:18.111
Chip reader's not working
so you can just slide.

17:18.146 --> 17:22.071
Wait, we don't live
on Hanover Court.

17:22.106 --> 17:24.612
Yep, 32 Hanover Court.

17:24.647 --> 17:26.317
Nope, we live on Donna Circle.

17:26.352 --> 17:26.878
You know what?

17:26.913 --> 17:27.747
Forget it.

17:27.782 --> 17:28.484
Just forget the loyalty.

17:28.519 --> 17:29.122
Wait.

17:29.157 --> 17:30.255
Oh.

17:30.290 --> 17:31.949
Oh, I see.

17:31.984 --> 17:34.127
There's two Maggie Moores in
the system, the one at Hanover

17:34.162 --> 17:35.656
and then you guys on Donna.

17:35.691 --> 17:38.395
And then somehow the system
just like-- oh, wait.

17:38.430 --> 17:40.793
No, it didn't switch it.

17:40.828 --> 17:42.267
It's just under that one phone.

17:42.302 --> 17:44.137
That is so weird.

17:44.172 --> 17:45.028
I wonder how that happened.

17:48.704 --> 17:50.902
You never finished
telling me about your date,

17:50.937 --> 17:52.178
the co-ed from class.

17:55.645 --> 17:57.249
OK, first of all,
it wasn't a date.

17:57.284 --> 18:00.417
And second of all, she's a
grown woman with two kids.

18:00.452 --> 18:02.155
OK, what's wrong with that?

18:02.190 --> 18:03.651
I didn't say anything
was wrong with her.

18:06.656 --> 18:08.084
OK, this is going
to sound weird--

18:08.119 --> 18:10.196
I mean really sound weird.

18:10.231 --> 18:11.527
Lay it on me.

18:11.562 --> 18:12.957
Lay it on me?

18:12.992 --> 18:14.464
What are you?

18:14.499 --> 18:15.663
You're in the
