spontaneous combustion.

23:33.378 --> 23:34.520
So let me get this straight.

23:34.555 --> 23:36.753
In your scenario
here, this person

23:36.788 --> 23:39.690
drives off the highway down
some random embankment,

23:39.725 --> 23:42.924
stops here, and spontaneously
bursts into flames?

23:42.959 --> 23:44.189
Can't even tell you the sex.

23:44.224 --> 23:45.696
Too badly burned.

23:45.731 --> 23:47.533
An accelerant was used,
though, and plenty of it.

23:47.568 --> 23:51.537
Ah, so not
spontaneous combustion.

23:51.572 --> 23:53.429
I'll get you
more from the lab.

23:53.464 --> 23:54.034
Thank you.

23:58.843 --> 24:02.174
You know, KB, that was
a person who died there,

24:02.209 --> 24:05.848
murdered in a horrible,
horrible fashion.

24:05.883 --> 24:06.882
I know.

24:06.917 --> 24:08.653
Why do you got to make jokes?

24:08.688 --> 24:09.478
It's not right.

24:09.513 --> 24:10.215
It's not respectful.

24:10.250 --> 24:12.019
Don't do it, OK?

24:12.054 --> 24:13.218
Yeah.

24:13.253 --> 24:14.989
Did you pull a
VIN off the car?

24:15.024 --> 24:16.958
No, dash and doors too melted.

24:16.993 --> 24:18.454
Did you check the battery?

24:18.489 --> 24:20.764
Sometimes there's a
serial number plate.

24:25.166 --> 24:26.198
Yeah, see?

24:26.233 --> 24:26.902
There.

24:26.937 --> 24:27.496
Yeah.

24:27.531 --> 24:29.135
Run that.

24:29.170 --> 24:31.907
