26:43.744 --> 26:46.712
[laughs] OK.

26:46.747 --> 26:50.507
Well, you know, you're welcome
to take the shaker home

26:50.542 --> 26:52.113
and show her what
she's been missing.

26:52.148 --> 26:55.347
Uh, yeah.

26:55.382 --> 26:58.922
She passed away
about a year ago.

27:01.828 --> 27:03.487
Oh, I'm sorry about that.

27:07.592 --> 27:09.735
I'm divorced if you
were wondering why I drag

27:09.770 --> 27:12.199
strangers in to eat with me.

27:12.234 --> 27:14.498
[laughs] Well, you
must have friends.

27:14.533 --> 27:16.071
Oh, god, no.

27:16.106 --> 27:19.206
They all chose him, and frankly,
I can't make the effort.

27:19.241 --> 27:20.977
I've been trying to
pal up to Maggie.

27:21.012 --> 27:22.539
We'll see where that goes.

27:22.574 --> 27:23.507
She seems nice.

27:23.542 --> 27:25.850
Her husband's a little off.

27:25.885 --> 27:29.546
I'm finding it takes courage
to be happy, you know?

27:29.581 --> 27:31.449
I'm just not sure my
ex left me with any.

27:36.456 --> 27:37.092
I don't know.

27:37.127 --> 27:39.160
I bet you--

27:39.195 --> 27:41.228
I bet you have plenty.

27:41.263 --> 27:43.230
No, he broke me
down pretty good.

27:43.265 --> 27:48.741
[laughs]

27:48.776 --> 27:52.272
Well, where do
you think I might

27:52.307 --> 27:54.604
