27:54.639 --> 27:55.847
Come on, man.

27:55.882 --> 27:57.013
It's my prom.

27:57.048 --> 27:59.213
Yeah, and prom's
a huge night for us.

27:59.248 --> 28:01.545
Yeah, but like who eats subs?

28:01.580 --> 28:04.581
Anyway, like, we're all dressed
up to go to real restaurants.

28:04.616 --> 28:05.791
Yeah, and you smoke weed.

28:05.826 --> 28:08.387
You get wasted and unpacked.

28:08.422 --> 28:09.190
Sorry, Greg.

28:09.225 --> 28:10.961
I can't spare you.

28:10.996 --> 28:12.424
[knocking]

28:24.273 --> 28:24.876
Hey there, officer.

28:24.911 --> 28:25.536
Mr. Moore.

28:25.571 --> 28:26.735
Yeah, yeah.

28:26.770 --> 28:27.472
Mind if I talk to
you for a second?

28:27.507 --> 28:27.978
Yeah, of course.

28:31.115 --> 28:31.949
No, no.

28:31.984 --> 28:33.445
No, that can't be right.

28:33.480 --> 28:36.118
It's possible there's
a mistake, no?

28:36.153 --> 28:37.713
When was the last
time you saw your wife?

28:37.748 --> 28:41.552
I was just over
to work on the yard.

28:41.587 --> 28:44.489
So you two were
living separately then?

28:44.524 --> 28:48.328
We had like a stupid
fight, and I tried

28:48.363 --> 28:49.835
calling her today to apologize.

28:49.870 --> 28:52.596
I even went to the diner
where she works, you know,

28:52.631 --> 28:56.765
trying to make up.

28:56.800 --> 28:58.767
Who would do this?

28:58.802 --> 29:02.078
Everybody just loved Mags.

29:02.113 --> 29:03.508
She was a rock star.

29:08.053 --> 29:10.779
We'll find out
sooner or later.

29:10.814 --> 29:11.516
We always do.

29:14.620 --> 29:16.356
I'm very sorry for
your loss, Mr. Moore.

29:24.135 --> 29:25.266
I'm sorry for your loss.

29:25.301 --> 29:29.006
[door banging open]

29:29.041 --> 29:30.007
