33:43.922 --> 33:44.492
It's me.

33:51.897 --> 33:54.238
[tv playing loudly]

33:55.670 --> 33:58.473
Why is it--

33:58.508 --> 33:59.111
[tv shutting off]

33:59.146 --> 34:00.112
[bang]

34:00.147 --> 34:01.036
Jesus!

34:01.071 --> 34:02.004
OK, sorry.

34:05.009 --> 34:08.043
MAN (ON TV): Let me
take a whack at it.

34:08.078 --> 34:09.319
Demented fuck.

34:14.986 --> 34:21.727
So, just asking, no disrespect,
because I know you're like--

34:21.762 --> 34:26.567
but I pretty clearly said
scare her, not, you know,

34:26.602 --> 34:29.339
set her on fucking fire.

34:29.374 --> 34:40.185
So like-- yeah.

34:40.220 --> 34:41.450
Yeah, that sounds like Maggie.

34:41.485 --> 34:44.112
Jesus Christ.

34:44.147 --> 34:47.654
So was she, like,
alive when you--

34:50.989 --> 34:51.955
Well, thank God for that.

34:55.059 --> 34:57.862
So I got the cops fucking
knocking on my door, man.

34:57.897 --> 35:00.271
So I got a plan.

35:00.306 --> 35:02.031
You know my wife's
name, Maggie, right?

35:02.066 --> 35:04.275
Maggie Moore.

35:04.310 --> 35:07.135
Well, there's another Maggie
Moore, same exact fucking name,

35:07.170 --> 35:09.214
only a couple of miles away.

35:09.249 --> 35:15.352
So what I'm thinking
is if we-- you--

35:15.387 --> 35:19.114
remove the second
Maggie Moore, it'll

35:19.149 --> 35:22.623
make it look like the
first removal, my Maggie,

35:22.658 --> 35:26.121
was just a mistake,
like it was an accident.

35:26.156 --> 35:27.056
And I'm off the hook.

35:31.865 --> 35:35.339
I mean, they're not twins, but.

35:38.839 --> 35:39.409
Yeah?

35:53.260 --> 35:55.326
You didn't say anything
about me, right?

35:55.361 --> 35:55.953
To Maggie?

36:08.704 --> 36:10.770
Fuck.

36:10.805 --> 36:13.245
What the hell?

36:13.280 --> 36:14.708
Why would you tell her that?

36:14.743 --> 36:15.940
[shredding]

36:15.975 --> 36:16.875
Jesus Christ.

36:22.146 --> 36:26.291
PASTOR: Maggie, as you
all know, loved children,

36:26.326 --> 36:29.591
but not having been blessed
with children of her own,

36:29.626 --> 36:33.298
she feared her life
would be without meaning.

36:33.333 --> 36:35.223
It was not.

36:35.258 --> 36:37.093
Maggie was able to
find new meaning

36:37.128 --> 36:39.304
through her work at the diner.

36:39.339 --> 36:40.899
Why are you making me do this?

36:40.934 --> 36:42.736
Why do you make me
interrupt my route to come

36:42.771 --> 36:44.804
here to get what's mine, huh?

36:44.839 --> 36:46.707
Finder's fee ain't much,
not the way you were talking

36:46.742 --> 36:47.774
what a divorce would cost.

36:50.614 --> 36:51.448
Come on, man.

36:51.483 --> 36:52.779
I got to be the pastor.

36:52.814 --> 36:54.715
Right, because otherwise
you'll go to hell.

36:54.750 --> 36:55.980
Like, that's why you'll go.

37:08.764 --> 37:10.896
PASTOR: --and the truth of our
relationships with our friends

37:10.931 --> 37:15.670
and loved ones, the
truth within ourselves.

37:15.705 --> 37:19.740
You see, life is not about
the houses we live in,

37:19.775 --> 37:23.645
the cars we drive,
or the money we make.

37:23.680 --> 37:26.318
In times like these,
we realize that only

37:26.353 --> 37:28.749
three things truly matter--

37:28.784 --> 37:32.522
our health, our
family, and our faith.

37:32.557 --> 37:33.952
[phone vibrating]

37:37.155 --> 37:39.188
Police Chief Sanders?

37:39.223 --> 37:42.125
Did I interrupt you
refilling the pepper grinder?

37:42.160 --> 37:44.765
No, no, pepper refills are
performed at 10:00 and 6:00

37:44.800 --> 37:45.634
daily.

37:45.669 --> 37:46.965
I'm good for the night.

37:47.000 --> 37:51.134
[chuckles] Hey, listen.

37:51.169 --> 37:55.941
I was thinking, would
you want to maybe get

37:55.976 --> 37:58.515
some ice cream or something?

37:58.550 --> 38:00.011
I could come by if
it's not too late.

38:03.313 --> 38:05.456
Is that a yes, then?

38:05.491 --> 38:06.457
I'll pick you up?

38:06.492 --> 38:07.491
Sure.

38:07.526 --> 38:08.217
See you in a bit.

38:20.363 --> 38:21.901
Is yours as good as it looks?

38:21.936 --> 38:24.541
I'm not sharing.

38:24.576 --> 38:26.136
Hey, you know a decent mechanic?

38:26.171 --> 38:29.040
Because my dash is like
all warning lights.

38:29.075 --> 38:31.306
Uh, I do, actually.

38:31.341 --> 38:32.582
Who won't cheat me?

38:32.617 --> 38:33.979
Oh, no, he'll
definitely cheat you.

38:34.014 --> 38:35.849
But his work is solid.

38:40.889 --> 38:42.823
You know, I know we don't really
know each other that well,

38:42.858 --> 38:44.429
but I feel like something
might be bothering you.

38:44.464 --> 38:45.529
Am I wrong?

38:48.798 --> 38:52.998
When you were at my house, you
obviously knew Maggie was gone.

38:53.033 --> 38:55.539
We had a whole
conversation that--

38:55.574 --> 38:59.235
I don't know-- I just think
it's a little strange.

38:59.270 --> 39:00.709
And you're annoyed?

39:00.744 --> 39:03.338
Absolutely not annoyed.

39:03.373 --> 39:05.615
Mildly put out.

39:05.650 --> 39:07.243
That's fair.

39:07.278 --> 39:09.916
That I didn't tell you
about Maggie's murder

39:09.951 --> 39:11.918
before I told her husband.

39:11.953 --> 39:13.689
It was just
strange, like I said,

39:13.724 --> 39:16.626
to see the news that night and
think back on our conversation

39:16.661 --> 39:18.595
and how you didn't say a word.

39:18.630 --> 39:21.895
I am obligated to
inform the next of kin

39:21.930 --> 39:23.193
before the next door neighbor.

39:23.228 --> 39:24.194
Whatever.

39:24.229 --> 39:24.898
I'm always the last to know.

39:37.979 --> 39:38.780
You have a lot that's--

39:38.815 --> 39:40.243
[laughs]

39:40.278 --> 39:41.211
Yeah, there you go.

39:41.246 --> 39:41.816
Thank you.

39:45.756 --> 39:46.689
Want to go for a walk?

39:51.256 --> 39:53.465
Then I see him come out of the
bathroom with this other guy.

39:53.500 --> 39:56.259
And Jim looks like he's been
shoved around a little bit.

39:56.294 --> 39:57.799
And then the other
guy just roars

39:57.834 --> 39:59.163
off in this delivery truck.

39:59.198 --> 40:00.131
I don't know.

40:00.166 --> 40:01.429
I just thought it was odd.

40:01.464 --> 40:02.430
Hey, do you like to gamble?

40:02.465 --> 40:03.937
Because I work at the casino.

40:03.972 --> 40:05.070
And I don't know-- if you
ever wanted to come up--

40:05.105 --> 40:06.610
Hold on, go back.

40:06.645 --> 40:10.174
So Jay misses the beginning
of his wife's funeral

40:10.209 --> 40:12.440
because he's been shoved
around by some guy

40:12.475 --> 40:14.585
that drives the delivery truck?

40:14.620 --> 40:16.015
It was odd, right?

40:16.050 --> 40:19.524
See, I'm usually so not
even close on this stuff.

40:19.559 --> 40:24.452
Did you happen to see the
name on the side of the truck?

40:24.487 --> 40:26.927
Maybe there's
security footage?

40:26.962 --> 40:27.963
I watch a lot of SVU.

40:31.032 --> 40:31.800
Liberty.

40:31.835 --> 40:33.263
Liberty Bell Foods.

40:33.298 --> 40:36.673
I remember the bell.

40:36.708 --> 40:38.136
Junior detective.

40:41.174 --> 40:43.438
Hey, look who's
a sex offender.

40:43.473 --> 40:44.373
I didn't do nothing.

40:44.408 --> 40:45.110
Why am I here?

40:45.145 --> 40:45.979
Child porn?

40:46.014 --> 40:47.145
That's nothing to you?

40:47.180 --> 40:48.982
You can't arrest
me on that again.

40:49.017 --> 40:52.183
That's eminent domain.

40:52.218 --> 40:55.318
Well, you got us there,
Tommy T. What do you

40:55.353 --> 40:58.156
and Jay Moore have going
on at the sandwich shop?

40:58.191 --> 40:58.959
Nothing's going.

40:58.994 --> 40:59.960
What?

40:59.995 --> 41:01.632
With Liberty Bell Foods?

41:01.667 --> 41:03.634
Jay buys from you,
instead of corporate.

41:03.669 --> 41:04.569
Pro tip.

41:04.604 --> 41:06.461
We already know.

41:06.496 --> 41:07.836
Hey, you don't know shit.

41:07.871 --> 41:09.134
Why don't you go back to France?

41:09.169 --> 41:11.169
Leave us hard-working
Americans alone.

41:11.204 --> 41:14.843
Keep in mind you're in
a massive shitstorm here.

41:14.878 --> 41:17.648
[sighs] And it's all expired.

41:17.683 --> 41:20.508
They're just going to throw
that shit out anyways.

41:20.543 --> 41:21.883
The chips?

41:21.918 --> 41:25.480
Yeah, the chips, the
meat, cheese, all of it.

41:25.515 --> 41:31.486
So Jay buys expired food from
you and sells it at his place?

41:31.521 --> 41:32.861
That is so disgusting.

41:32.896 --> 41:34.929
And what do you
get out of this?

41:34.964 --> 41:38.163
Nothing, a couple of bucks.

41:38.198 --> 41:40.770
Well, see, we heard that
Jay and his wife Maggie

41:40.805 --> 41:42.871
got in a big fight right
before she was murdered,

41:42.906 --> 41:45.269
and the word "filth" came up.

41:45.304 --> 41:48.910
So I'm wondering, maybe in
exchange for this cheap,

41:48.945 --> 41:53.112
expired food, Jay provided
you with some form

41:53.147 --> 41:55.510
of sexual gratification
that you're not allowed

41:55.545 --> 41:56.852
to have in your possession?

41:56.887 --> 41:58.414
You sick fuck.

41:58.449 --> 41:59.217
Uh-uh.

41:59.252 --> 42:00.053
That's crazy.

42:00.088 --> 42:01.417
False.

42:01.452 --> 42:03.122
That's why she kicks
him out of the house.

42:03.157 --> 42:05.388
That's why she
initiates the divorce.

42:05.423 --> 42:06.961
You kill Maggie
Moore, Tommy T?

42:06.996 --> 42:07.698
Me?

42:07.733 --> 42:09.557
No fucking way!

42:09.592 --> 42:11.295
Maybe you know somebody
in that line of work.

42:11.330 --> 42:12.428
No, no, man.

42:12.463 --> 42:14.529
I swear on my mom's life.

42:14.564 --> 42:16.201
See, I know I
should believe you

42:16.236 --> 42:17.708
because you're such
an upstanding citizen,

42:17.743 --> 42:18.874
but I don't know.

42:18.909 --> 42:20.744
I'm starting to
warm to my theory.

42:20.779 --> 42:23.780
[ominous music]

42:49.269 --> 42:53.678
Please, take my bag.

42:53.713 --> 42:54.305
Take my jewelry.

42:58.311 --> 43:00.751
There's credit cards in there.

43:00.786 --> 43:02.049
I can give you the pins.

43:05.890 --> 43:08.616
Would you mind if I
kept my insulin kit?

43:08.651 --> 43:09.991
I have diabetes.

43:10.026 --> 43:10.860
It's not worth anything.

43:13.733 --> 43:16.426
Here, here.

43:16.461 --> 43:19.396
[dramatic music]

43:44.654 --> 43:46.324
[screaming] Help me!

43:46.359 --> 43:49.360
[crying]

44:05.917 --> 44:09.754
You got the other
Maggie, too, right?

44:09.789 --> 44:12.086
Did you make her think
you'd let her go, too?

44:17.357 --> 44:19.654
Fuck you, you twisted
piece of shit!

44:19.689 --> 44:20.292
Oh!

44:46.958 --> 44:48.452
[gunshot]

44:59.399 --> 45:00.068
Wow.

45:00.103 --> 45:02.070
You know what?

45:02.105 --> 45:06.041
They just-- there's this new
invention they came up with.

45:06.076 --> 45:07.570
It's called a car wash.

45:07.605 --> 45:09.814
And what they do is they
take all of the dirt off

45:09.849 --> 45:10.980
of the outside of
the car, and then

45:11.015 --> 45:12.113
you can see what color it is.

45:12.148 --> 45:13.147
Huh.

45:13.182 --> 45:15.281
I can't see that catching on.

45:15.316 --> 45:16.447
Really?

45:16.482 --> 45:18.053
You're not an
investor, I hope.

45:18.088 --> 45:20.088
So I changed the oil, and
the tire pressure was low.

45:20.123 --> 45:23.795
And the gas sensor was
the passenger side airbag.

45:23.830 --> 45:25.896
You need a new one.

45:25.931 --> 45:27.095
How much?

45:27.130 --> 45:29.724
3,200 plus tax.

45:29.759 --> 45:31.902
For a passenger airbag?

45:31.937 --> 45:34.399
I can't think of anyone
that I like that much.

45:34.434 --> 45:36.500
Yeah, that's a pass.

45:36.535 --> 45:37.072
All right.

45:37.107 --> 45:37.842
Sorry.

45:37.877 --> 45:38.909
Give me a minute.

45:38.944 --> 45:39.503
Thanks, Bud.

45:39.538 --> 45:41.076
Boss.

45:41.111 --> 45:41.846
3,200?

45:41.881 --> 45:43.144
That's nuts.

45:43.179 --> 45:44.772
Well, to be fair,
I did say Buddy would

45:44.807 --> 45:47.951
most likely try to cheat you.

45:47.986 --> 45:51.020
Oh, uh, I got to go.

45:51.055 --> 45:52.252
Are you going to be OK here?

45:52.287 --> 45:53.022
Yeah.

45:53.057 --> 45:54.518
You heard the man.

45:54.553 --> 45:55.992
Half of my air bags are
in perfect working order.

45:56.027 --> 45:57.752
Go be a policeman.

45:57.787 --> 46:00.590
Police chief,
thank you very much.

46:00.625 --> 46:01.965
Fancy badge.

46:02.000 --> 46:02.658
I'll call you later.

46:06.070 --> 46:07.938
Wash your car.

46:07.973 --> 46:09.269
Wash your ass.

46:09.304 --> 46:11.469
I heard that.

46:11.504 --> 46:13.438
[siren]

46:13.473 --> 46:16.276
The vehicle's registered to
Maggie Moore, lives a few miles

46:16.311 --> 46:17.145
from here.

46:17.180 --> 46:18.311
You say Maggie Moore?

46:18.346 --> 46:20.016
Weird, right?

46:20.051 --> 46:22.480
Two dead Maggie
Moores one week apart.

46:22.515 --> 46:23.613
Yeah, that's weird.

46:23.648 --> 46:24.251
Hey, chief.

46:31.326 --> 46:34.129
First Maggie's a mistake, so
he chops off this ring finger

46:34.164 --> 46:36.560
to prove he got it right?

46:36.595 --> 46:37.869
Prove to who?

46:37.904 --> 46:39.464
I'm thinking the husband.

46:39.499 --> 46:41.499
I mean, who else
would know the ring?

46:41.534 --> 46:42.665
That's assuming
she was married

46:42.700 --> 46:44.876
and assuming she wore a ring.

46:44.911 --> 46:47.703
We don't know any of that.

46:47.738 --> 46:50.244
Imagine that conversation,
the husband telling the guy he

46:50.279 --> 46:51.410
killed the wrong Maggie Moore.

46:51.445 --> 46:52.147
You're sure?

46:52.182 --> 46:53.214
Yeah, I'm sure.

46:53.249 --> 46:54.743
She's right here
making meatloaf.

46:54.778 --> 46:56.811
It would mean Tommy T
and Jay are off the hook.

46:56.846 --> 46:59.418
Yeah, and the end of the whole
Liberty Bell Foods conspiracy.

46:59.453 --> 47:01.057
I know how much you wanted
to make that happen.

47:06.262 --> 47:08.933
Did your wife
wear a wedding ring?

47:08.968 --> 47:10.759
Yes, matching.

47:10.794 --> 47:12.200
Can I get a picture, please?

47:15.700 --> 47:18.008
Got it.

47:18.043 --> 47:21.374
What can you
tell us, Mr. Moore?

47:21.409 --> 47:23.112
Anything going on in her life?

47:23.147 --> 47:25.015
Duane Rich.

47:25.050 --> 47:29.118
If you want to know who
did this, Duane Rich.

47:29.153 --> 47:30.845
OK?

47:30.880 --> 47:34.288
He worked with Maggie, just
gave her nothing but trouble.

47:34.323 --> 47:36.092
Made her life goddamn miserable.

47:36.127 --> 47:37.225
Was this at the credit union?

47:37.260 --> 47:38.589
Yeah.

47:38.624 --> 47:39.458
What kind of trouble
are we talking about?

47:39.493 --> 47:41.196
Hate crime stuff.

47:41.231 --> 47:44.397
He would leave like notes
with swastikas on her desk.

47:44.432 --> 47:46.102
She would come back from
lunch, and there would be

47:46.137 --> 47:48.203
like a web page open to ovens.

47:48.238 --> 47:49.435
KB: Because you're Jewish.

47:49.470 --> 47:50.634
Well, no shit
because she's Jewish.

47:53.837 --> 47:55.606
She went to HR.

47:55.641 --> 47:58.081
They finally fired his ass.

47:58.116 --> 48:01.051
Was there any concern on
her part with this Duane Rich

48:01.086 --> 48:04.384
that her life might
actually be in danger?

48:04.419 --> 48:07.123
She asked me for a gun.

48:07.158 --> 48:08.784
That's how scared she was.

48:08.819 --> 48:11.721
But I talked her out of it.

48:11.756 --> 48:13.459
I told her that she
was overreacting.

48:13.494 --> 48:15.164
The guy was just a bully.

48:18.004 --> 48:20.895
I was supposed to protect her.

48:20.930 --> 48:21.764
Look what I did.

48:26.210 --> 48:28.309
Seemed legit.

48:28.344 --> 48:30.014
Well, just because he
feels bad doesn't mean

48:30.049 --> 48:30.806
he didn't do it.

48:38.453 --> 48:40.321
Ma'am, please, I
got nothing to say.

48:40.356 --> 48:42.026
Another woman was
murdered with the same name

48:42.061 --> 48:42.950
as your wife.

48:42.985 --> 48:43.621
You must have an opinion.

48:43.656 --> 48:44.919
My opinion?

48:44.954 --> 48:46.327
My opinion is that
I am grief stricken.

48:46.362 --> 48:48.857
And you should be
ashamed of yourself.

48:48.892 --> 48:50.793
Jesus Christ.

48:50.828 --> 48:52.927
Sorry about the
ruckus here, sir.

48:52.962 --> 48:53.763
I got this, Greg.

48:53.798 --> 48:56.667
Take out the trash.

48:56.702 --> 48:58.042
What are we having today, sir?

48:58.077 --> 49:03.542
Uh, turkey provolone
foot long on wheat.

49:03.577 --> 49:05.808
All right.

49:05.843 --> 49:06.677
Turkey provolone.

49:06.712 --> 49:07.876
How's your day going?

49:07.911 --> 49:08.547
Excellent.

49:08.582 --> 49:09.449
Yeah?

49:09.484 --> 49:11.451
You win the mega ball?

49:11.486 --> 49:12.221
Yeah, I'm just kidding.

49:36.874 --> 49:39.347
[clearing throat]

49:39.382 --> 49:40.876
Something wrong, sir?

49:45.685 --> 49:46.486
Seriously?

49:46.521 --> 49:47.322
You went undercover?

49:47.357 --> 49:48.224
This isn't our meat.

49:48.259 --> 49:49.159
This isn't our cheese.

49:49.194 --> 49:50.259
This isn't our produce.

49:50.294 --> 49:51.755
These aren't even
our snack chips.

49:51.790 --> 49:55.924
What you do have
is a lot of mold.

49:55.959 --> 49:59.862
Yeah, that's avocado,
I'm pretty sure.

49:59.897 --> 50:03.371
You're in breach of your
franchise agreement, Mr. Moore.

50:03.406 --> 50:06.704
Look, man, I
just lost my wife.

50:06.739 --> 50:09.872
The poor woman was murdered.

50:09.907 --> 50:11.280
I'm sorry for your loss.

50:11.315 --> 50:12.743
I am.

50:12.778 --> 50:14.085
But this is a serious violation.

50:14.120 --> 50:14.712
I know.

50:14.747 --> 50:16.087
I know.

50:16.122 --> 50:17.847
But can you just, like,
do me a solid human

50:17.882 --> 50:21.389
being a human being?

50:21.424 --> 50:22.588
I didn't even get
to say goodbye.

50:22.623 --> 50:23.754
She was burned up so bad.

50:27.331 --> 50:29.925
$600.

50:29.960 --> 50:31.729
Sorry?

50:31.764 --> 50:32.862
You're asking me to help you.

50:32.897 --> 50:34.600
I'm helping you.

50:34.635 --> 50:36.866
For $600?

50:36.901 --> 50:41.442
What price would you put on
keeping your shop open, huh?

50:41.477 --> 50:43.609
Get the fuck out.

50:43.644 --> 50:45.941
That's my fucking price?

50:45.976 --> 50:48.449
Get out of my shop, man.

50:48.484 --> 50:49.714
Go!

50:49.749 --> 50:51.320
Are you fucking
serious with this, man?

50:51.355 --> 50:52.882
OK.

50:52.917 --> 50:54.422
I'm a goddamn widower!

51:03.631 --> 51:04.201
Shit.

51:14.675 --> 51:15.278
Hey, hey.

51:18.217 --> 51:20.283
I'm sorry.

51:20.318 --> 51:21.647
It's been a rough
couple of weeks.

51:24.190 --> 51:25.189
600.

51:37.632 --> 51:38.202
Duane Rich?

51:43.209 --> 51:45.132
I don't know
what you've heard.

51:45.167 --> 51:48.311
Well, I'll tell you what
we've heard, Mr. Rich.

51:48.346 --> 51:50.940
Maggie's husband said that
you continuously harassed

51:50.975 --> 51:54.350
her and were anti-Semitic.

51:54.385 --> 51:56.946
And HR said that you
were fired from your job

51:56.981 --> 51:59.718
for those very reasons.

51:59.753 --> 52:02.688
Well, here's the thing is,
I don't dispute any of that.

52:05.528 --> 52:07.121
The way I behaved,
it was shameful.

52:07.156 --> 52:10.795
And I am mortified by it.

52:10.830 --> 52:13.501
Then why did you do it?

52:13.536 --> 52:19.309
Well, because I was a drunk.

52:19.344 --> 52:21.311
I'm an alcoholic.

